cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with statistical spoken dialogue systems and dialogue modelling. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel dialogue model that is centred around entities and is able to model relations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses training a policy using relations and comparing it to a baseline. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with spoken dialogue systems. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses the benefits of relation modelling on the dialogue level and how the system is capable of processing relations present in the user input.
